post_text: STSD Superintendent, Dr. Tamara Willis, and School Board President Jesse Gantt will be joining the call to provide tools and resources to best educate children during the state-mandated school closure due to COVID-19.
shared_text:
PA State Rep. Sue Helm
April 28 at 10:41 AM ¬∑

On Thursday, April 30, at 5:50 p.m., I will be hosting a telephone town hall to help address your concerns with the COVID-19 pandemic. I will be joined by Dr. Tamara Willis, Susquehanna Township School District (STSD) superintendent; Jesse Gantt, STSD School Board president; and Dr. John Goldman, an infectious disease specialist at UPMC Harrisburg.

Dr. Willis and Mr. Gantt will help provide tools and resources you can use to best educate your children while schools are closed due to quarantine, and Dr. Goldman will provide practices you can use to stay safe and healthy during the pandemic as well as professional medical advice.

Shortly before the call begins, an invitation call will go out to landlines in the district. If you prefer to call in yourself, you can do so by dialing 877-229-8493 and entering the ID code 15051.

The call can also be streamed live online, here: https://video.teleforumonline.com/video/streaming.php?client=5051
text:
STSD Superintendent, Dr. Tamara Willis, and School Board President Jesse Gantt will be joining the call to provide tools and resources to best educate children during the state-mandated school closure due to COVID-19.

PA State Rep. Sue Helm
April 28 at 10:41 AM ¬∑

On Thursday, April 30, at 5:50 p.m., I will be hosting a telephone town hall to help address your concerns with the COVID-19 pandemic. I will be joined by Dr. Tamara Willis, Susquehanna Township School District (STSD) superintendent; Jesse Gantt, STSD School Board president; and Dr. John Goldman, an infectious disease specialist at UPMC Harrisburg.

Dr. Willis and Mr. Gantt will help provide tools and resources you can use to best educate your children while schools are closed due to quarantine, and Dr. Goldman will provide practices you can use to stay safe and healthy during the pandemic as well as professional medical advice.

Shortly before the call begins, an invitation call will go out to landlines in the district. If you prefer to call in yourself, you can do so by dialing 877-229-8493 and entering the ID code 15051.

The call can also be streamed live online, here: https://video.teleforumonline.com/video/streaming.php?client=5051

post_text: This morning, STHS had the honor of hosting Attorney General Shaprio for the third installment of the Teen Talk series. 60 high school seniors from STHS, CD East, and HBG SD joined the AG for an open discussion about bulling and cyber-bullying prevention and coping skills. The series of round tables were held across the Commonwealth and will result in a student-driven report with recommendations as reported by the student participants. Our student ambassadors demonstrated incredible insight, courage and leadership. #hannaproud

After careful consideration of feedback and concerns regarding the timeliness of this notice and it‚Äôs impact on staff and families, the district has decided to remain closed on President's Day, and therefore, we will not be in session on Monday February 18th.

As a reminder, school will be in session on April 17th and 18th as a result of of prior weather related closures.

We do apologize for any confusion that this may have caused. If you have any questions, please call 717-657-5100. Thank you.

post_text: The annual HANNA Powder Puff flag football game, honoring the memory of Zach Holtzman and sponsored by and benefiting the HANNA Foundation, happens Tues, Nov 20, 7pm at STHS. Admission is $3 for students & $5 for adults. Donations of blankets and non perishable holiday food for the items will be accepted to benefit Adopt-a-Family at Thomas Holtzman Elementary.

post_text: Thank you PA State Rep. Sue Helm for recognizing the STHS School of the Arts Fashion Design Program! The students were proud to present their creations during the Susquehanna Township Alumni Association breakfast, which was held in early October.
shared_text:
PA State Rep. Sue Helm
October 26, 2018 at 1:38 PM ¬∑

I had the opportunity to spend some time with a very talented group of Susquehanna Township High School students. They're in the fashion design program taught by Richard Andries (far right in the group photo).

I am so impressed by these kids, who are wearing the clothing they created. Congratulations to all and well done!
